      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "- **New Features**\r\n\t- **Week numbers in calendar**: Added a new \"Week numbers\" setting that displays week numbers in the calendar view. You can choose from four calculation methods: ISO 8601, Western traditional, Middle Eastern, or Auto (based on your \"Week start\" setting). Defaults to off.\r\n-  **Bug Fixes**\r\n\t- Fixed incorrect date replacement when using multiple date formats.\r\n\t  Previously, if the cursor was on a date like \"05/23/2026\" and you selected format 1 (`mm/dd`) in the modal, only the inner portion \"05/23\" was replaced, leaving \"/2026\" as a leftover. Now the widest matching date at the cursor is always used as the replacement target, regardless of which format button is selected. This also applies when the cursor is on a format 1 date and you select format 2 — the matched text is replaced rather than the new date being inserted alongside the old one.\r\n\t- Fixed an issue where dates outside the current month were not visually dimmed in dark theme.\r\n- Minor internal improvements.",
