      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "##  New Feature\r\n\r\n- **Automatically select date text under cursor**\r\n  When opening the calendar, if the cursor is on text that matches a supported date format, that matching text will be automatically selected.\r\n  This makes updating dates much faster and more convenient, without needing to manually select them.\r\n\r\n## New Option\r\n\r\n- **`Default date on calendar open`**  \r\n  Choose which date is selected when opening the calendar:  \r\n  - `Today`\r\n  - `Selected date`\r\n  *(default: `Today`)*\r\n\r\n## Example\r\nDemonstrates the new feature \"Default date on calendar open\" together with the new option \"Selected date\".\r\n![demo](https://github.com/namikaze-40p/obsidian-date-inserter/blob/main/demo/ver-0.6.0/auto-select-date-text-under-cursor.gif)\r\n\r\n## Thanks\r\nSpecial thanks to @alexmkv for contributing the \"Automatically select date text under cursor\" feature in [#10](https://github.com/namikaze-40p/obsidian-date-inserter/pull/10).",
